<eesti> Artikkel 1 </eesti>
<inglise> The purpose of the Directive is to put into effect the framework agreement on fixed-term contracts concluded on 18 March 1999 between the general cross-industry organisations (ETUC, UNICE and CEEP) annexed hereto. </inglise>
<eesti> K&auml;esoleva direktiivi eesm&auml;rk on j&otilde;ustada t&ouml;&ouml;andjate ja t&ouml;&ouml;v&otilde;tjate vaheliste &uuml;ldorganisatsioonide (ETUC, UNICE ja CEEP) vahel 18. m&auml;rtsil 1999 s&otilde;lmitud raamkokkulepe t&auml;htajaliste t&ouml;&ouml;lepingute kohta, mis on direktiivile lisatud. </eesti>
<inglise> Article 2 </inglise>
<eesti> Artikkel 2 </eesti>
<inglise> Member States shall bring into force the laws, regulations and administrative provisions necessary to comply with this Directive by 10 July 1999, or shall ensure that, by that date at the latest, management and labour have introduced the necessary measures by agreement, the Member States being required to take any necessary measures to enable them at any time to be in a position to guarantee the results imposed by this Directive. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid j&otilde;ustavad k&auml;esoleva direktiivi j&auml;rgimiseks vajalikud normid 10. juuliks 1999 v&otilde;i tagavad, et hiljemalt sel kuup&auml;eval on t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooled kehtestanud vajalikud meetmed kokkuleppe teel, kusjuures liikmesriigid peavad v&otilde;tma vajalikud meetmed, et t&ouml;&ouml;suhte pooled saaksid igal ajal tagada k&auml;esolevas direktiivis etten&auml;htud tulemuste saavutamise. </eesti>
<inglise> They shall forthwith inform the Commission thereof. </inglise>
<eesti> Liikmesriigid teatavad sellest viivitamata komisjonile. </eesti>
<inglise> Member States may have a maximum of one more year, if necessary, and following consultation with management and labour, to take account of special difficulties or implementation by a collective agreement. </inglise>
